#Text=Sam Brownback on running for President , gay rights , the Middle East and religion
#Text=This article mentions the Wikimedia Foundation , one of its projects , or people related to it .
#Text=Wikinews is a project of the Wikimedia Foundation .
#Text=Monday , October 15 , 2007
#Text=Sam Brownback is perplexed .

#Text=The U.S. Senator from Kansas and Presidential candidate is a Republican whose politics — he is against marriage for gay people , he is against abortion , and he has a clean image in a party tainted by scandal — should speak favorably to the party 's base .
#Text=But it has not .
#Text=" I 'm baffled by that myself , " Senator Brownback told Wikinews reporter David Shankbone .
#Text=" We have n't been able to raise money . "
#Text=A recent poll in Iowa has put him in eighth place , with 2 % supporting his campaign .
#Text=" If we do n't finish fourth or better in Iowa ...

#Text=Although he does n't feel  competent " to explain why God would dislike gays , he does feel strongly that allowing two men or two women to enter into the union of marriage will destroy it for heterosexuals .

column1: #Text=Pointing to the research of Stanley Kurtz at the Hoover Institution , Brownback asserts that Northern Europeans have " taken the sacredness out of the institution . "

#Text=In the interview , Senator Brownback discusses the tug-and-pull that befalls him when his constituents show up at his office and say , " Look , I 'm a conservative , but we need this bridge , we need this subsidy , we need this hospital . ”

column1: #Text=However , there is a debate over whether the process to make corn ethanol uses more energy than the ethanol itself produces .
#Text=Below is David Shankbone 's interview with Senator Sam Brownback .
#Text=On running in and possibly leaving the Presidential race
#Text=Senator Brownback , how are you ?
#Text=I 'm fine ; headed into Iowa .
#Text=I ’m doing a big event with Joe Biden tomorrow on a political solution in Iraq .
